This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a machine learning model for feature extraction from sensor data. It also involves the use of deep learning techniques such as sequence-to-sequence models. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed model involves learning universal and meaningful features that can be applied to similar tasks. 

The paper also involves the analysis of human behavior, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). 

As the paper involves the use of sensors and data analysis, it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

Finally, the paper proposes the use of semi-supervised learning, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
